SUMMARY:🥖🏛️ ST. LAWRENCE MARKET WALK & LUNCH 🏛️🥖
DESCRIPTION:Try New Things in Toronto!\n🥖🏛️ ST. LAWRENCE MARKET WALK & LUNCH 🏛️🥖\nHistory\, Hallways & Some of the Best Food in Canada\n\nIf you want to understand Toronto\, you don’t start with the skyline.\nYou start with **St. Lawrence Market**.\n\nWidely considered one of the most beloved markets in Canada\, St. Lawrence Market isn’t just a place to grab lunch — it’s woven into the foundation of the city itself. The original market dates back to the early 1800s and was one of the first public gathering spaces in what would become Toronto. Markets were where the city happened — where food was sold\, announcements were made\, and community life unfolded.\nFun fact? The building complex has worn many hats over the years. The area once housed Toronto’s first City Hall — and yes\, even a jail. Imagine that: politicians upstairs\, prisoners downstairs\, and fresh produce somewhere in between. Only in early Toronto.\n\nToday\, it remains one of the most celebrated food markets in the country — a place where old-school butchers\, fishmongers\, bakers\, cheesemakers\, and global food vendors operate side by side. It’s lively\, layered\, and delicious.\nAnd we’re going to experience it together.\n\n👉 **Don’t forget to join our WhatsApp group** – [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi018gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🚶‍♂️ The Walk There\n\nWe’ll begin at the subway station and walk down Broadview\, making our way along Queen East\, over to King\, and eventually down to Front Street.\nIt’s a relaxed urban walk — a chance to chat\, stretch our legs\, and build a little anticipation before the feast.\nPlease only sign up if you’re comfortable walking in rain or colder weather. This event runs unless conditions are extreme.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🥟 The Food Plan\nOnce we arrive\, we’ll explore both the café area and the main food market.\nExpect options like:\n\n🥪 Peameal bacon sandwiches\n🧀 Local Ontario cheeses\n🥐 Fresh pastries\n🦞 Seafood counters\n🌮 International eats\n🍁 Maple treats\n\nDon’t forget to bring some cash — a few vendors are still old-school and cash-only.\nThe plan: grab whatever calls your name and then find a table to sit and eat together. No pressure\, no fixed menu — just good food and good company.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🧢 Meetup Details\n📍 Meetup Location: Right outside the subway station\n🫎 I’ll be wearing my Moose Hat\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11:00 AM\n❗ We will only wait 5 minutes\n\nEnd Stop: Front & Lower Jarvis\nYou’re welcome to leave at any time.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🎟️ **Meetup Fee:** $5 cash in person **or** e-transfer to\n📧 \\*\\*[mathewmaclean@hotmail.com**](http://mathewmaclean@hotmail.com%2A%2A/)\n\nThis fee helps support the group and allows us to keep hosting events like this. Thank you for supporting community! 💖\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🌈 Who Is This For?\nThis group is open to anyone who wants to be social and make friends — whether single or not.\n\nWe also host:\n🎬 Movies\n🚶 Walks & hikes\n🎭 Arts & culture outings\n🍽️ Restaurant gatherings\n\nThere’s always something happening.\nAnd remember — you can just show up on the day if you’re unsure about your schedule.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n⚠️ A Gentle Reminder\nSometimes life happens and plans shift — please keep an eye out for updates in case of cancellation.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n👤 Organizer: Mathew\nQuestions? Post on the event wall or email\n📧 [torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com](mailto:torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com)\n\nCome for the history.\nStay for the food.\nLeave understanding Toronto just a little bit better — and probably carrying a pastry for later.\nThere’s something magical about eating in a place where the city has been gathering for over 200 years.\nLet’s go taste it. 🥖✨
